ock jcpenney plans to put minimartha stewart shops in many of its stores in  as well as starting a website together in january  the companys chief operating officer at the time michael kramer revealed to the wall street journal that more than  percent of the bandwidth of jcpenneys headquarters was used for the viewing of youtube videos during that month alone kramer consequently laid off  employees to change the companys workplace culture on february   jcpenney began a new pricing method with every day prices on most days reflecting what used to be sale prices monthly value for certain items every month in place of sales and best price the first and third fridays of each month tied to paydays prices would also not end in  or  instead using whole figures when pricing items the changes in the stores include a focus on the ministores such as those for martha stewart products in april  the company announced plans to trim its workforce laying off nearly  of its home office staff in dallas and closing a call center in pittsburgh many managers supervisors and longtime employees were let go on april   in june  the company announced that michael francis the companys president was leaving the company after only eight months on the job effective immediately in july  the company announced that it was laying off  more workers at its headquarters in august  jcpenney began rolling out a shops strategy in stores the shops are described as storeswithinastore planning to eventually roll out  shops in  stores the first shops include levis the original arizona jean co and i jeans by buffalo that month the company posted a second quarter comparablestore loss of  with internet sales dropping  at an analyst meeting in new york the same day johnson said im completely convinced that our transformation is on track jcpenneys stock rose  on johnsons comments at the analyst meeting the largest singleday stock increase since late january  fourth quarter sales for jcpenney in  were poor sales were off  from a year earlier same store sales were down  strategic choices made by johnson a year earlier including the change in pricing strategy were being called into question it was announced in april  that nickelson wooster would become the creative director for jcpenney menswear wooster stated in an interview with esquire that his influence on the brand would begin with spring menswear available as of february  on april   johnson was fired from jcpenney after  months with the company mike ullman the retailers former ceo was announced as his replacement shortly afterwards—the official statement claimed that ullman was wellpositioned to quickly analyze the situation jcpenney faces and take steps to improve the companys performance in august  william a ackman of pershing square capital management continued his efforts to remove thomas engibous the companys chairman of the board of directors however ackman resigned from the board on august   and two new directors were subsequently appointed to the board one of whom is former macys vice chairman ronald tysoe in his statement ackman stated during my time on the jcpenney board of directors i have always advocated for what i believe to be in the best interests of the company—its stockholders employees and others at this time i believe that the addition of two new directors and my stepping down from the board is the most constructive way forward for jcpenney and all other parties involved on september   jcpenney with goldman sachs as the sole underwriter announced plans to issue  million shares of its stock the move stood in contrast with ceo mike ullmans remarks from earlier that day whereby he did not foresee conditions for the rest of the year that would warrant raising liquidity  during a november  conference call to wall street analysts ullman announced that jcp is restoring initial markups necessary to support the return to a promotional department store strategy with gross margins currently  percent of sales versus  percent a year ago were lower due to the impact of clearance sales to eliminate inventory overhang and to transition back to the promotional pricing strategy the company is known for ullman is removing the radio frequency identification technology and returning to security tags because shrinkage has added  basis points on margins in the third quarter various analysts have mixed reviews of jcps future on december   jc penney was replaced by allegion in the sp  index sp cited jc penneys  fall in market value to  billion equivalent to  billion in  was more representative of the midcap market jc penney replaced aéropostale from the sp midcap  index in  soros fund management sold over  million jcp shares after only owning them for a few months –presentedit on january   jc penney announced it is closing  underperforming stores and laying off  employees ceo mike ullman explained in a news release as we continue to progress toward longterm profitable growth it is necessary to reexamine the financial performance of our store portfolio and adjust our national footprint accordingly jc penneys stock has continued its decline until their first quarter results in  showed signs of improvement and sent the share value back into the double digits in october  it was announced that the company would be tapping former home depot executive marvin ellison to take on the role of ceo starting in november  in january  it was announced that jcpenney would close  underperforming stores nationwide and layoff  employees that same year the company announced that it was liquidating its the foundry big  tall supply co chain of standalone clothing stores in january  jc penney announced plans to relaunch its business of selling major appliances for kitchens and laundry rooms the company moved away from selling major appliances in  but it now plans to return to this business in an effort to target a wave of millennials who are buying firsttime homes in february  jc penney announced that it would shutter two distribution centers and up to  underperforming stores as it wrestles with disappointing sales the company also plans to offer buyouts for roughly  employees on march   jc penney released a list of  locations that would close by the end of june  by closing stores and distribution facilities jc penney will redirect resources to help expand its storeinstore sephora boutiques and add nike and adidas boutiques similar to what macys has done with finish line lids and lenscrafters corporate identityedit in june  an ad called speed dressing emerged ending with the jcpenney logo and slogan every day matters the ad won a prize at the cannes lions international advertising festival the ad was criticized for seeming to promote teen sex jcpenney denied that the ad was theirs and their advertising agency saatchi  saatchi reported that it had been created by a third party vendor it was entered in the competition by epoch films who declined to comment marketing expert john tantillo advised that the company distance itself from the commercial and also shed the publicity it engendered logoedit penneys logo used from  to  current jcpenney logo originally used from  to  and reintroduced in  jcpenney box logo – alternate jcpenney logo used on a few stores used from  until  jcpenney logo used from  until   j c penney private brands labelsedit jc penney introduced its own private brands when some suppliers denied access to the expected inventories some of jcpenney brands are ana worthington st johns bay the original arizona jean company ambrielle stafford j ferrar jf xersion and jcpenney home™ st johns bay casual mens and womens clothing and shoes the original arizona jean company everyday casual clothing and sandals for men women and children xersion active and athletic clothing for men women and children stafford mens tailored clothing mens suits and other formal apparel and shoes j ferrar jf mens full line of clothing from mens suits and formal shoes to sandals worthington 