and decline  –present  corporate identity  logo  j c penney private brands labels  see also  references  external links historyedit – early history and incorporationedit jc penney mother store in kemmerer wyoming in september  james cash penney was born in hamilton missouri after graduating from high school penney worked for a local retailer he relocated to colorado at the advice of a doctor hoping that a better climate would improve his health in  penney went to work for thomas callahan and guy johnson who owned dry goods stores called golden rule stores in colorado and wyoming in  callahan sent penney to evanston wyoming to work with johnson in another golden rule store callahan and johnson asked penney to join them in opening a new golden rule store using money from savings and a loan penney joined the partnership and moved with his wife and infant son to kemmerer wyoming to start his own store penney opened the store on april   he participated in the creation of two more stores and purchased full interest in all three locations when callahan and johnson dissolved their partnership in  in  penney moved his company headquarters to salt lake city utah to be closer to banks and railroads by  penney had  stores in the rocky mountain states in  all stores were consolidated under the jc penney banner the socalled mother store in kemmerer opened as the chains second location in  it still operates as of  albeit with shorter hours than many other locations in  the company was incorporated under the new name j c penney company with william henry mcmanus as a cofounder in  the headquarters was moved to new york city to simplify buying financing and transportation of goods by  the company operated  stores in  states in the united states j c penney acquired the crescent corset company in  the companys first wholly owned subsidiary in  the companys oldest active private brand big mac work clothes was launched the company opened its th store in  in hamilton missouri james cash penneys hometown by the opening of the th store in  gross business had reached  equivalent to  billion in  in  sam walton began working at a j c penney in des moines iowa walton later went on to found future retailer walmart in  by  jc penney operated  stores in all  states in  j c penney started national advertising with a series of advertisements in life magazine j c penney credit cards were first issued in  – growth and successedit penney building in anchorage in  following the earthquake former downtown seattle store in  with signage from the period when the chain was branded as penneys and used a more stylized font in its logo pike place market is in the background in  j c penney entered discount merchandising with the acquisition of general merchandise company which gave them the treasury stores these discount operations proved unsuccessful and were shuttered in  in  j c penney issued its first catalog the company operated instore catalog desks in eight states the catalogs were distributed by the milwaukee catalog distribution center the company dedicated its first fullline shopping center department store in  this store was located at black horse pike center in audubon new jersey the second full line shopping center store was dedicated at king of prussia plaza in king of prussia pennsylvania in late  those stores expanded the lines of merchandise and services that an average j c penney carried to include appliances sporting goods garden merchandise restaurants beauty salons portrait studios auto parts and auto centers j c penney expanded to include alaska and hawaii in the s the company opened stores in anchorage and fairbanks alaska in  the penney building in anchorage partially collapsed and was damaged beyond repair in the  alaska earthquake the company rebuilt the store as a shorter building on a larger footprint and followed up by building anchorages first public parking garage which opened in  in  j c penney finished its national expansion with the open