  jcpenney sold their directmarketing insurance unit to dutch insurer aegon for  billion equivalent to  billion in  in cash this was an attempt to allow the company to focus on the retail business in  the company added  more stores and exited the drug store division after  years with the sale of its eckerd division in  jcpenneys ecommerce storefront exceeded the onebillion dollar revenue mark for the first time in  jcpenney launched the ambrielle lingerie label which became their largest private brand launched in the companys history j c penney also reintroduced cosmetics with the opening of sephora storeswithinastore inside some j c penney locations beginning in  the store slogan changed from its all inside to every day matters the new slogan and associated ad campaign was launched in television commercials during the th academy awards in late february  jcpenney financial services direct marketing division was sold off in the early s this ruler was given to employees to emphasize the golden rule after jcpenney sold off eckerd in  the locations that continued to operate as eckerd some locations in the southern us were sold to cvs corporation still had jcpenney catalog centers inside the stores which was a carryover from locations that were once thrift drug and also continued to accept jcpenney credit cards after rite aid finalized its acquisition of eckerd in  the catalog centers inside the soontobeconverted stores permanently closed although as a result of the acquisition rite aid now accepts jcpenney credit cards even at rite aid locations that existed before the takeover of eckerd in november  the company launched a new public website jcpenneybrandscom which covers the companys private and exclusive brands and their branding strategy with a preview of an upcoming product line in february  the company launched the american living brand as developed by ralph lauren across several product lines including mens womens and childrens apparel and shoes intimate apparel and home the launch which was accompanied by an ad campaign during the  academy awards was the companys largest private brand launch american living for infant apparel was launched in july  in the summer of  j c penney also added a new brand to its home collection linden street the linden street brand features a contemporary lifestyle collection of furniture domestics and home decor linden street is sold exclusively in jcpenney stores and through their website other new exclusive brands for juniors and young mens were launched in the summer of  they included a relaunch of le tigre along with decree and fabulosity a junior line of clothing by kimora lee simmons in july  new additions were made to the jcpenney young mens department including an expansion of their private brand decree previously exclusively a juniors clothing line and the introduction of more skatesurforiented clothing including rusty rs by ryan sheckler and rd rail in august  albert gonzalezs defense lawyer announced jcpenney was a victim of the computer hacker although jcpenney stated that no customers credit card information had been stolen in september  jcpenney had joined facebook to help promote their care share win campaign since  jcpenney has donated  million to after school care fans of jcpenney on facebook can help decide which school will receive the next million dollars in  jcpenney reached an agreement with seattles best coffee to feature fullservice cafes within leased departments inside jcpenney stores across the country currently seattles best coffee are still expanding cafe locations within jcpenney locations across the country – rebranding and declineedit a twostory j c penney at stonebriar centre in frisco texas in january  opened in  jc penney offices in salt lake city utah on january   jcpenney announced it would exit the catalog business and close all  of its catalog outlet stores an additional seven stores two call center facilities and one customer decorating facility would also be closed one of the jcpenney outlet stores that closed at franklin mills mall now philadelphia mills mall in philadelphia pa was replaced on march   by a regular jcpenney store it was announced on march   that this store would be one of the  to close on february   the new york times exposed the companys use of link schemes—spamdexing—to increase the jcpenney web sites ranking in google search results especially during the holiday season doug pierce an expert in online search described the optimization as the most ambitious attempt to game googles search results that he has ever seen ultimately google took retaliatory action and drastically reduced the visibility of jcpenney in searches although the retailer denied any involvement it fired its search engine consulting firm searchdex in june  jcpenney announced that ron johnson who had led apple retail stores in a period of high growth became the companys new ceo in october  jcpenney sold the  remaining catalog outlet stores to sb capital group these stores will remain open then transition to jcs  star outlets on december   jcpenney announced the acquisition of  percent of martha stewart living omnimedia stock jcpenney plans to put minimartha stewart shops in many of its stores in  as well as starting a website together in january  the companys chief operating officer at the time michael kramer revealed to the wall street journal that more than  percent of the bandwidth of jcpenneys headquarters was used for the viewing of youtube videos during that month alone kramer consequently laid off  employees to change the companys workplace culture on february   jcpenney began a new pricing method with every day prices on most days reflecting what used to be sale prices monthly value for certain items every month in place of sales and best price the first and third fridays of each month tied to paydays prices would also not end in  or  instead using whole figures when pricing items the changes in the stores include a focus on the ministores such as those for martha stewart products in april  the company announced plans to trim its workforce laying off nearly  of its home office staff in dallas and closing a call center in pittsburgh many managers supervisors and longtime employees were let go on april   in june  the company announced that michael francis the companys president was leaving the company after only eight months on the job effective immediately in july  the company announced that it was laying off  more workers at its headquarters in august  jcpenney began rolling out a shops strategy in stores the shops are described as storeswithinastore planning to eventually roll out  shops in  stores the first shops include levis the original arizona jean co and i jeans by buffalo that month the company posted a second quarter comparablestore loss of  with internet sales dropping  at an analyst meeting in new york the same day johnson said im completely convinced that our transformation is on track jcpenneys stock rose  on johnsons comments at the analyst meeting the largest singleday stock increase since late january  fourth quarter sales for jcpenney in  were poor sales were off  from a year earlier same store sales were down  strategic choices made by johnson a year earlier including the change in pricing strategy were being called into question it was announced in april  that nickelson wooster would become the creative director for jcpenney menswear wooster stated in an interview with esquire that his influence on the brand would begin with spring menswear available as of february  on april   johnson was fired from jcpenney after  months with the company mike ullman the retailers former ceo was announced as his replacement shortly afterwards—the official statement claimed that ullman was wellpositioned to quickly analyze the situation jcpenney faces and take steps to improve the companys performance in august  william a ackman of pershing square capital management continued his efforts to remove thomas engibous the companys chairman of the board of directors however ackman resigned from the board on august   and two new directors were subsequently appointed to the board one of whom is former macys vice chairman ronald tysoe in his statement ackman stated during my time on the jcpenney board of directors i have always advocated for what i believe to be in the best interests of the company—its stockholders employees and others at this time i believe that the addition of two new directors and my stepping down from the board is the most constructive way forward for jcpenney and all other parties involved on september   jcpenney with goldman sachs as the sole underwriter announced plans to issue  million shares of its stock the move stood in contrast with ceo mike ullmans remarks from earlier that day whereby he did not foresee conditions for the rest of the year that would warrant raising liquidity  during a november  conference call to wall street analysts ullman announced that jcp is restoring initial markups necessary to support the return to a promotional department store strategy with gross margins currently  percent of sales versus  percent a year ago were lower due to the impact of clearance sales to eliminate inventory overhang and to transition back to the promotional pricing strategy the company is known for ullman is removing the radio frequency identification technology and returning to security tags because shrinkage has added  basis points on margins in the third quarter various analysts have mixed reviews of jcps future on december   jc penney was replaced by allegion in the sp  index sp cited jc penneys  fall in market value to  billion equivalent to  billion in  was more representative of the midcap market jc penney replaced aéropostale from the sp midcap  index in  soros fund management sold over  million jcp shares after only owning them for a few months –presentedit on january   jc penney announced it is closing  underperforming stores and laying off  employees ceo mike ullman explained in a news release as we continue to progress toward longterm profitable growth it is necessary to reexamine the financial performance of our store portfolio and adjust our national footprint accordingly jc penneys stock has continued its decline until their first quarter results in  showed signs of improvement and sent the share value back into the double digits in october  it was announced that the company would be tapping former home depot executive marvin ellison to take on the role of ceo starting in november  in january  it was announced that jcpenney would close  underperforming stores nationwide and layoff  employees that same year the company announced that it was liquidating its the foundry big  tall supply co chain of standalone clothing stores in january  jc penney announced plans to relaunch its business of selling major appliances for kitchens and laundry rooms the company moved away from selling major appliances in  but it now plans to return to this business in an effort to target a wave of millennials who are buying firsttime homes in february  jc penney announced that it would shutter two distribution centers and up to  underperforming stores as it wrestles with disappointing sales the company also plans to offer buyouts for roughly  employees on march   jc penney released a list of  locations that would close by the end of june  by closing stores and distribution facilities jc penney will redirect resources to help expand its storeinstore sephora boutiques and add nike and adidas boutiques similar to what macys has done with finish line lids and lenscrafters corporate identityedit in june  an ad called speed dressing emerged ending with the jcpenney logo and slogan every day matters the ad won a prize at the cannes lions international advertising festival the ad was criticized for seeming to promote teen sex jcpenney denied that the ad was theirs and their advertising agency saatchi  saatchi reported that it had been created by a third party vendor it was entered in the competition by epoch films who declined to comment marketing expert john tantillo advised that the company distance itself from the commercial and also shed the publicity it engendered logoedit penneys logo used from  to  current jcpenney logo originally used from  to  and reintroduced in  jcpenney box logo – alternate jcpenney logo used on a few stores used from  until  jcpenney logo used from  until   j c penney private brands labelsedit jc penney introduced its own private brands when some suppliers denied access to the expected inventories some of jcpenney brands are ana worthington st johns bay the original arizona jean company ambrielle stafford j ferrar jf xersion and jcpenney home™ st johns bay casual mens and womens clothing and shoes the original arizona jean company everyday casual clothing and sandals for men women and children xersion active and athletic clothing for men women and children stafford mens tailored clothing mens suits and other formal apparel and shoes j ferrar jf mens full line of clothing from mens suits and formal shoes to sandals worthington womens formal and casual clothing and shoes ana young womens urban clothing and shoes ambrielle womens sleepwear and intimates jcpenney home™ goods for home see alsoedit dallasfort worth portal companies portal j c penneychicago store tucson arizona listed on the national register of historic places nrhp j c penney company building shoshone idaho nrhplisted j c penney co warehouse building st louis missouri nrhplisted j c penney building newberg oregon nrhplisted j c penney historic district kemmerer wy a us national historic landmark j c penney house kemmerer wyoming nrhplisted referencesedit  a b jcpenney form q for the quarterly period ended october   pdf us securities and exchange commission retrieved april      form k j c penneycompany inc united states securities and exchange commission march   retrieved apri