ectations jc penney names home depot executive as its next chief the company tapping a seasoned retail hand said marvin ellison would become president in november and chief executive next august by hiroko tabuchi return to traditions spurs optimism at j c penney the retailer which just two years ago appeared to be teetering on the brink of collapse says it is now back on sound footing walmart jc penney and other retailers see a tentative shopper walmart’s domestic sales were flat instead of falling penney’s sharply cut its losses and kohl’s sales and profit fell macy’s gave a forecast that will hinge on customer sentiment by elizabeth a harris advertising jc penney burnishes its liz claiborne brand after some years of zigzagging in promoting claiborne penney’s wants to project it as a multigenerational brand aiming for yearold women as well as longtime fans by stuart elliott business briefing j c penney files appeal in macy’s contract case the company appealed a new york state court ruling that found it had interfered with a contract between macy’s and martha stewart living omnimedia by selling the celebrity’s home goods ruling against jc penney in dispute with macy’s over martha stewart products the ruling that jc penney unlawfully interfered with a merchandising agreement may be the penultimate chapter of a longrunning dispute among three famous names in retailing by hilary stout show more skip to navigation search articles  results for sorted by newest department stores once anchors at malls become millstones macy’s and sears have recently announced numerous closings reflecting a climate in which online and discount retailers have outmaneuvered them by sapna maheshwari kenneth axelson who troubleshot new york city’s fiscal crisis dies at  the city enlisted mr axelson an executive of j c penney as a deputy mayor in  to help balance its budget and stave off bankruptcy by sam roberts bargainhunting frenzy threatens traditional department stores as macy’s nordstrom a